# Implementation Plan - Phase 8: Ratings, Reviews & Notifications

This plan details the design and changes to implement course reviews with rating aggregations, real-time in-app notification alerts over WebSockets, and mock SMTP email dispatching.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Signals-based Rating Cache**: We will add a `rating_average` field to the `Course` model to store the computed average rating. Django post-save and post-delete signals on the `Review` model will automatically update this field. This is much faster than computing averages dynamically during list queries.
> - **In-App WebSockets Consumer**: A new route `/ws/notifications/` will be routed to a notification consumer using JWT authentication. Notifications will be pushed live to the student or mentor's specific user channel group `user_{user_id}`.
> - **Console Email Backend**: For local development, we configure the console email backend (`django.core.mail.backends.console.EmailBackend`) which will print out dispatched emails directly to the Django server console without requiring setup of real mail servers.

